Title: Carbon Copy / Madhouse

reviewText: This review is only for Madhouse- Don't confuse this with the awful horror movies by the same name.  This is great comedy.I really love this movie and have been waiting for it to come out on DVD.  By itself, it is reason enough to spend the money on this 'double feature'.  I had "Madhouse" on laser disc years ago but donated that collection to a library years ago.  This is one of the movies I have not been able to replace on DVD until now.- If you like John Larroquette,- If you like Kirstie Alley,- If you like seeing snobby yuppies getting taken down a peg or too,- If you like cats,- If you hate cats,...Then this movie is for you. There is a hysterical running gag about the cat!Now I can check off another one from my movie bucket list.
Title: Carbon Copy / Madhouse

reviewText: I am appreciative that Amazon bought one of my all time favorite movies to me but I wish it was on a regular DVD. Anyway, I only bought the set for Madhouse, haven't watched carbon copy yet. Madhouse is about a couple who has everything under control until an unexpected visit from cousins occurs. From the moment the cousins step off of the plane everything rolls down hill. This movie makes you never want to have company....
